        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 53ba9bf200c173dda9213f90e9896ad0419970dd\nparent e16b0c08710b5901be7a6a0aa672c34d34ddc928\nauthor will <will@256k1.dev> 1770025682 +0000\ncommitter will <will@256k1.dev> 1770026009 +0000\n\nci: improve ccache hitrate across CI runs\n\nccache defaults may contribute to cache invalidation between CI runs.\nUse additional configuration to try and get more hits:\n\n- compiler_check=mtime: Docker image rebuilds give the compiler a new\n  mtime even when the version is unchanged, invalidating all entries.\n\nInclude two belt-and-suspenders settings (which should in theory not be\nan issue beetween runs):\n\n- hash_dir=true: the working directory is included in the hash, so\n  any path difference between runners causes misses\n- No base_dir: absolute paths aren't normalized, compounding the\n  path sensitivity.\n",
